Father accused of hanging 4 siblings in Durban arrested 4 September 2019 The man suspected of hanging his three young children and teen stepdaughter in Durban has been arrested. The Department of Social Development visited the overwhelmed family of the children on Wednesday in Copeville, Pietermaritzburg, and informed them of the news. KwaZulu-Natal police confirmed that a 44-year-old man was arrested in inKwadabeka and is facing four counts of murder. This is a developing story. News24